Well first of all, God told us that He is a jealous God:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You shall not make for yourself an idol in the form of anything in heaven above or on the earth beneath or in the waters below.  You shall not bow down to them or worship them; for I, the Lord your God, am a jealous God, punishing the children for the sin of the fathers to the third and fourth generation of those who hate me, but showing love to a thousand generations of those who love me and keep my commandments.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Exodus 20:4-6<br>
<br>
Second of all, we were created in the image of God and it stands to reason that there are traits which we possess which God also possesses.  The factor to keep in mind is that God is holy and perfect and our traits are warped by sin.  In 2 Corinthians, Paul wrote that he was jealous over people with a godly jealousy.  Godly jealousy and human jealousy are not the same thing.  Godly jealousy in equated to love.  Human jealousy is equated to selfishness.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Because some people are trying to force those commandments (such as the first one) on all of us.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
